{"title_page": "Franks Report (1957)", "text_new": "{{short description|Report by a British committee of inquiry}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2014}}\n\nThe '''Franks Report''' of 1957<ref>Paul Craig ''Administrative Law'', 6th edition</ref> was issued by a British committee of inquiry chaired by [[Oliver Franks, Baron Franks|Sir Oliver Franks]] in respect of growing concerns as to the range and diversity of tribunals, uncertainty about the procedures they followed and worry over lack of cohesion and supervision. The catalyst for this was the [[Crichel Down Affair]].<ref>(The affair of land being leased by the Ministry of Agriculture in the Attlee government instead of it being returned to its original owners as promised by Churchill).</ref> However, this was a result of a decision by the [[Government of the United Kingdom|British Government]] and the Franks committee was told to limit its discussion to formal [[Statute|statutory]] procedure and not to go into decisions of the [[court]]s or one-off decisions, which excluded the ''Crichel'' decision.\n\n==Basic assumptions of the report==\nTribunals are an adjudicating, rather than administrative, body and they should be fair, open and impartial.<ref>(Cmnd 218 (1957)).</ref> [[Openness]] is for publicity of proceedings and the reasoning behind the decision. [[Distributive justice|Fairness]] through having a clear procedure, allowing participants to present their case fully and knowledge of requirements to meet for parties. [[Impartiality]] established from independence from the real or apparent influence of the administration.\n\n==Aims and recommendations==\n===Constitution of tribunals===\nChairman to be chosen by the [[Lord Chancellor]], normally having legal qualifications for trial and mandatory for appellate tribunals. Rest of members to be chosen by the [[Administrative Justice and Tribunals Council|Council of Tribunals]].\n\n===Procedure of tribunals===\nThe Council of Tribunals should direct the particular procedure in each case, with the aim of combining order with an informal atmosphere. [[Citizen]]s should have a prior knowledge of the right to apply to participate and public knowledge of the proceedings unless the content is of sensitive nature, with legal representation normally allowed. Tribunals empowered to take evidence under oath, [[subpoena]] witnesses and award remedies. Decisions should give full reasons and a copy sent to all parties. Final appellate tribunal to publish its decision for lower tribunals. \n\n===Appeals from tribunal decisions===\n[[Appeal]] in the first instance should be to an appellate tribunal, but never to a [[Minister (government)|minister]] unless the First Instance tribunal is highly competent. [[Common law]] remedies of [[Certiorari]] (direction to send records), [[mandamus]] (mandatory order) and [[writ of prohibition]] (abstain a court where it lacks competence) should never be restricted. Also the report recommended that a Councils of Tribunals be formed to perform their respective role as envisaged in the report. \n\n==Achievements==\nMost of the recommendations were implemented by the Tribunals and Inquiries Act 1958 and [[Tribunals and Inquiries Act 1992]]; others were implemented by administrative practice.<ref>[http://www.lawteacher.net/Admin%20Tribunals.php Tribunals] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090421052441/http://www.lawteacher.net/Admin%20Tribunals.php |date=21 April 2009 }}</ref>\n\nWorking and number council of tribunal was mentioned in the schedules, with their function being advisory, but they could make recommendations on any matter and had to be consulted before any rule was enacted.\n\nRight to give reasons was added, but it had to be asked for before or during the decision, and judicial review restricted the right in a few instances. List of tribunals could be stopped by ministerial power.\n\nThe report\u2019s recommendations were not followed where appeals to the [[High Court]] ([[Court of Session]] in Scotland) were only permitted based on law and the procedure to appoint chairman and members.\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Public inquiries in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:1957 in British politics]]\n[[Category:United Kingdom tribunals]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Report by a British committe of inquiry}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2014}}\n\nThe '''Franks Report''' of 1957 <ref>Paul Craig ''Administrative Law'', 6th edition</ref> was issued by a British committee of inquiry chaired by [[Oliver Franks, Baron Franks|Sir Oliver Franks]] in respect of growing concerns as to the range and diversity of tribunals, uncertainty about the procedures they followed and worry over lack of cohesion and supervision. The catalyst for this was the [[Crichel Down Affair]].<ref>(The affair of land being leased by the Ministry of Agriculture in the Attlee government instead of it being returned to its original owners as promised by Churchill).</ref> However, this was a result of a decision by the [[Government of the United Kingdom|British Government]] and the Franks committee was told to limit its discussion to formal [[Statute|statutory]] procedure and not to go into decisions of the [[court]]s or one-off decisions, which excluded the ''Crichel'' decision.\n\n==Basic assumptions of the report==\nTribunals are an adjudicating, rather than administrative, body and they should be fair, open and impartial.<ref>(Cmnd 218 (1957)).</ref> [[Openness]] is for publicity of proceedings and the reasoning behind the decision. [[Distributive justice|Fairness]] through having a clear procedure, allowing participants to present their case fully and knowledge of requirements to meet for parties. [[Impartiality]] established from independence from the real or apparent influence of the administration.\n\n==Aims and recommendations==\n===Constitution of tribunals===\nChairman to be chosen by the [[Lord Chancellor]], normally having legal qualifications for trial and mandatory for appellate tribunals. Rest of members to be chosen by the [[Administrative Justice and Tribunals Council|Council of Tribunals]].\n\n===Procedure of tribunals===\nThe Council of Tribunals should direct the particular procedure in each case, with the aim of combining order with an informal atmosphere. [[Citizen]]s should have a prior knowledge of the right to apply to participate and public knowledge of the proceedings unless the content is of sensitive nature, with legal representation normally allowed. Tribunals empowered to take evidence under oath, [[subpoena]] witnesses and award remedies. Decisions should give full reasons and a copy sent to all parties. Final appellate tribunal to publish its decision for lower tribunals. \n\n===Appeals from tribunal decisions===\n[[Appeal]] in the first instance should be to an appellate tribunal, but never to a [[Minister (government)|minister]] unless the First Instance tribunal is highly competent. [[Common law]] remedies of [[Certiorari]] (direction to send records), [[mandamus]] (mandatory order) and [[writ of prohibition]] (abstain a court where it lacks competence) should never be restricted. Also the report recommended that a Councils of Tribunals be formed to perform their respective role as envisaged in the report. \n\n==Achievements==\nMost of the recommendations were implemented by the Tribunals and Inquiries Act 1958 and [[Tribunals and Inquiries Act 1992]]; others were implemented by administrative practice.<ref>[http://www.lawteacher.net/Admin%20Tribunals.php Tribunals] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090421052441/http://www.lawteacher.net/Admin%20Tribunals.php |date=21 April 2009 }}</ref>\n\nWorking and number council of tribunal was mentioned in the schedules, with their function being advisory, but they could make recommendations on any matter and had to be consulted before any rule was enacted.\n\nRight to give reasons was added, but it had to be asked for before or during the decision, and judicial review restricted the right in a few instances. List of tribunals could be stopped by ministerial power.\n\nThe report\u2019s recommendations were not followed where appeals to the [[High Court]] ([[Court of Session]] in Scotland) were only permitted based on law and the procedure to appoint chairman and members.\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Public inquiries in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:1957 in British politics]]\n[[Category:United Kingdom tribunals]]\n", "name_user": "Toweli", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Franks_Report_(1957)"}
{"title_page": "Annus horribilis", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Italic title}}\n'''''{{lang|la|Annus horribilis}}''''' is a [[Latin]] phrase, meaning \"horrible year\". It is complementary to ''{{lang|la|[[annus mirabilis]]}}'', which means \"wonderful year\"; however, ''annus mirabilis'' is a traditional term, while ''annus horribilis'' is of relatively recent coinage.\n\n==Origin of phrase==\nThe phrase ''annus horribilis'' was used in 1891 in an Anglican publication to describe 1870, the year in which the Roman Catholic church defined the dogma of [[papal infallibility]].<ref>{{cite book|title=London Quarterly and Holborn Review|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NpxJAQAAMAAJ|volume=75|year=1891|publisher=E.C. Barton|page=105|chapter=M\u00f6hler, D\u00f6llinger and Oxford Anglicanism}}</ref> \n\n== Elizabeth II ==\nThe expression was brought to modern prominence by United Kingdom's [[Queen Elizabeth II]] in a speech to [[Guildhall, London|Guildhall]] on 24 November 1992, marking the [[Ruby jubilee|40th anniversary]] of her accession, she said:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.royal.gov.uk/ImagesandBroadcasts/Historic%20speeches%20and%20broadcasts/Annushorribilisspeech24November1992.aspx |title=Annus horribilis speech, 24 November 1992 |publisher=The Official Website of the British Monarchy |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090302093837/http://www.royal.gov.uk/ImagesandBroadcasts/Historic%20speeches%20and%20broadcasts/Annushorribilisspeech24November1992.aspx |archivedate=2 March 2009 }}</ref>\n{{quote|1992 is not a year on which I shall look back with undiluted pleasure. In the words of one of my more sympathetic correspondents, it has turned out to be an ''annus horribilis''.}}\n\nThe \"sympathetic correspondent\" was later revealed to be her former assistant private secretary, [[Edward Ford (courtier)|Sir Edward Ford]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2006/nov/28/guardianobituaries.monarchy|title=Obituary: Sir Edward Ford|last=Corby|first=Tom|date=2006-11-28|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-09-11}}</ref> The unpleasant events which happened to the royal family in this year include:<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2012/may/24/royal-family-bounced-back-annus-horribilis How the royal family bounced back from its 'annus horribilis'], [[The Guardian]], 24 May 2012</ref>\n* Separation of the Queen's second son, [[Prince Andrew, Duke of York]], from his wife, [[Sarah, Duchess of York]] (19 March)\n* Divorce of the Queen's daughter, [[Anne, Princess Royal]], from [[Captain Mark Phillips]] (23 April)\n* Death by suicide of her nephew, Prince Albrecht of Hohenlohe-Langenburg (23 April)\n* Publication of [[Diana, Princess of Wales]]'s [[tell-all book]] ''Diana: Her True Story'', revealing the problems in her marriage to the Queen's eldest son, [[Charles, Prince of Wales]], particularly his affair with [[Camilla Parker Bowles]] (Sunday Times, 7 June 1992)\n* Publication of photographs of the Duchess of York sunbathing topless with her friend, John Bryan (20 August)\n* [[Squidgygate|Publication of intimate conversations]] between Diana, the Princess of Wales, and James Gilbey from a tape recording of their phone calls (24 August)\n* [[1992 Windsor Castle fire|Fire in Windsor Castle]], one of the Queen's official residences (20 November)\n* Separation of her son Charles, the Prince of Wales, and Diana (December)\n\n== Kofi Annan ==\n[[Kofi Annan]], then [[United Nations Secretary-General]], used the phrase in his year-end press conference on 21 December 2004. He reflected: \"There's no doubt that this has been a particularly difficult year, and I am relieved that this ''annus horribilis'' is coming to an end.\"<ref name=OffTheCuff>{{cite web | url = https://www.un.org/apps/sg/offthecuff.asp?nid=655 | title = New York, 21 December 2004 \u2013 Secretary-General's year-end press conference (unofficial transcript) | work = Off the Cuff | publisher = United Nations, Office of the Spokesman for the Secretary-General | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20050204001905/http://www.un.org/apps/sg/offthecuff.asp?nid=655 | archive-date=4 February 2005 }} The Secretary-General Off the Cuff</ref> His remarks were widely interpreted as having alluded to persistent allegations of corruption in the UN's Iraq [[Oil-for-Food Program]].<ref name=NineMSN>{{cite news |url=http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=23293 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050913182910/http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=23293 |archivedate=13 September 2005 |title=UN chief welcomes end of 'horrible' year |author=[[Associated Press]] |publisher=NineMSN |date=22 December 2004}}</ref> He also spoke of: upheaval and violence in [[2004 in Afghanistan|Afghanistan]], the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[2004 in Iraq|Iraq]], [[2004 in the Palestinian territories|Palestine]], and [[War in Darfur|Sudan]]; the ongoing process of UN internal reform; and \"persistent...criticism against the UN\" and himself personally.<ref name=OffTheCuff /><ref name=NineMSN /> Annan's remarks came five days before the deadliest event of the year (and one of the deadliest natural disasters in history), the [[Indian Ocean tsunami]] on 26 December.\n\n== Juan Carlos I ==\nIn 2007, the [[Spanish Royal Family]], in particular [[Juan Carlos I of Spain|King Juan Carlos I]], faced a difficult year. Family tragedy and a series of controversies led to Spanish newspapers to refer to the year as the king's ''annus horribilis''.<ref name=\"La Naci\u00f3n\">''[http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias_v2/site/artic/20071115/pags/20071115203346.html El \"annus horribilis\" del Rey Juan Carlos]''. {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121206025748/http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias_v2/site/artic/20071115/pags/20071115203346.html |date=6 December 2012 }}, [[La Naci\u00f3n]], 15 November 2007.</ref>\n* In February, \u00c9rika Ortiz Rocasolano, the youngest sister of [[Queen Letizia of Spain|Letizia, then the Princess of Asturias]], died of a drug overdose in her apartment.\n* In July, a humour magazine, ''[[El Jueves]]'', published a drawing that ran on the cover, depicting [[Felipe VI of Spain|Felipe, Prince of Asturias (now Felipe VI of Spain)]], and the aforementioned Princess Letizia having sex, with a caption reading: \"Just imagine if you end up pregnant. This will be the closest thing to work I\u2019ve ever done in my life.\" It satirized a proposal by the government to give 2,500 euros to the parents of newborn children. The magazine was banned and removed from distribution, which led to a censorship controversy.\n* In September, [[Catalonia|Catalan]] separatists were tried for having burned photographs of King Juan Carlos and [[Queen Sof\u00eda of Spain|Queen Sof\u00eda]] at an anti-monarchy and Catalan separatist rally in [[Girona]] while the royal couple toured the city.\n* In early November at the XVII [[Ibero-American Summit]], after a verbal altercation between [[Hugo Ch\u00e1vez]], [[President of Venezuela]], and [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez Zapatero]], [[Prime Minister of Spain]], the king asked Ch\u00e1vez, \"''[[\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 no te callas?]]''\" (\"Why don't you shut up?\").\n* Shortly after the summit, the royal house announced the separation of the king's daughter, the [[Infanta Elena, Duchess of Lugo|Duchess of Lugo]], and her husband, [[Jaime de Marichalar]]. The couple have two children, [[Felipe Juan Froil\u00e1n de Marichalar y Borb\u00f3n|Felipe]] and [[Victoria de Marichalar y Borb\u00f3n|Victoria]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Latin phrases]]\n* [[Rampjaar]], the Dutch \"disaster year\" of 1672\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wiktionary|annus horribilis}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090302093837/http://www.royal.gov.uk/ImagesandBroadcasts/Historic%20speeches%20and%20broadcasts/Annushorribilisspeech24November1992.aspx Royal.gov.uk \u2013 Transcript of The Queen's speech at Guildhall 24 November 1992]\n*[http://www.hodderheadline.co.uk/bookdetails.asp?book=110295 ''Annus Horribilis'']{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}: book by [[Sam Jordison]]\n\n{{Elizabeth II}}\n\n[[Category:Latin words and phrases]]\n[[Category:1992 in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Spanish monarchy]]\n[[Category:Elizabeth II]]\n[[Category:2007 in Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Italic title}}\n'''''{{lang|la|Annus horribilis}}''''' is a [[Latin]] phrase, meaning \"horrible year\". It is complementary to ''{{lang|la|[[annus mirabilis]]}}'', which means \"wonderful year\"; however, ''annus mirabilis'' is a traditional term, while ''annus horribilis'' is of relatively recent coinage.\n\n==Origin of phrase==\nThe phrase ''annus horribilis'' was used in 1891 in an Anglican publication to describe 1870, the year in which the Roman Catholic church defined the dogma of [[papal infallibility]].<ref>{{cite book|title=London Quarterly and Holborn Review|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NpxJAQAAMAAJ|volume=75|year=1891|publisher=E.C. Barton|page=105|chapter=M\u00f6hler, D\u00f6llinger and Oxford Anglicanism}}</ref> \n\n== Elizabeth II ==\nThe expression was brought to modern prominence by United Kingdom's [[Queen Elizabeth II]] in a speech to [[Guildhall, London|Guildhall]] on 24 November 1992, marking the [[Ruby jubilee|40th anniversary]] of her accession, she said:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.royal.gov.uk/ImagesandBroadcasts/Historic%20speeches%20and%20broadcasts/Annushorribilisspeech24November1992.aspx |title=Annus horribilis speech, 24 November 1992 |publisher=The Official Website of the British Monarchy |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090302093837/http://www.royal.gov.uk/ImagesandBroadcasts/Historic%20speeches%20and%20broadcasts/Annushorribilisspeech24November1992.aspx |archivedate=2 March 2009 }}</ref>\n{{quote|1992 is not a year on which I shall look back with undiluted pleasure. In the words of one of my more sympathetic correspondents, it has turned out to be an ''annus horribilis''.}}\n\nThe \"sympathetic correspondent\" was later revealed to be her former assistant private secretary, [[Edward Ford (courtier)|Sir Edward Ford]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2006/nov/28/guardianobituaries.monarchy|title=Obituary: Sir Edward Ford|last=Corby|first=Tom|date=2006-11-28|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-09-11}}</ref> The unpleasant events which happened to the royal family in this year include:<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2012/may/24/royal-family-bounced-back-annus-horribilis How the royal family bounced back from its 'annus horribilis'], [[The Guardian]], 24 May 2012</ref>\n* Separation of the Queen's second son, [[Prince Andrew, Duke of York]], from his wife, [[Sarah, Duchess of York]] (19 March)\n* Divorce of the Queen's daughter, [[Anne, Princess Royal]], from [[Captain Mark Phillips]] (23 April)\n* Death by suicide of her nephew, [[Gottfried, Prince of Hohenlohe-Langenburg|Prince Albrecht of Hohenlohe-Langenburg]] (23 April)\n* Publication of [[Diana, Princess of Wales]]'s [[tell-all book]] ''Diana: Her True Story'', revealing the problems in her marriage to the Queen's eldest son, [[Charles, Prince of Wales]], particularly his affair with [[Camilla Parker Bowles]] (Sunday Times, 7 June 1992)\n* Publication of photographs of the Duchess of York sunbathing topless with her friend, John Bryan (20 August)\n* [[Squidgygate|Publication of intimate conversations]] between Diana, the Princess of Wales, and James Gilbey from a tape recording of their phone calls (24 August)\n* [[1992 Windsor Castle fire|Fire in Windsor Castle]], one of the Queen's official residences (20 November)\n* Separation of her son Charles, the Prince of Wales, and Diana (December)\n\n== Kofi Annan ==\n[[Kofi Annan]], then [[United Nations Secretary-General]], used the phrase in his year-end press conference on 21 December 2004. He reflected: \"There's no doubt that this has been a particularly difficult year, and I am relieved that this ''annus horribilis'' is coming to an end.\"<ref name=OffTheCuff>{{cite web | url = https://www.un.org/apps/sg/offthecuff.asp?nid=655 | title = New York, 21 December 2004 \u2013 Secretary-General's year-end press conference (unofficial transcript) | work = Off the Cuff | publisher = United Nations, Office of the Spokesman for the Secretary-General | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20050204001905/http://www.un.org/apps/sg/offthecuff.asp?nid=655 | archive-date=4 February 2005 }} The Secretary-General Off the Cuff</ref> His remarks were widely interpreted as having alluded to persistent allegations of corruption in the UN's Iraq [[Oil-for-Food Program]].<ref name=NineMSN>{{cite news |url=http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=23293 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050913182910/http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=23293 |archivedate=13 September 2005 |title=UN chief welcomes end of 'horrible' year |author=[[Associated Press]] |publisher=NineMSN |date=22 December 2004}}</ref> He also spoke of: upheaval and violence in [[2004 in Afghanistan|Afghanistan]], the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[2004 in Iraq|Iraq]], [[2004 in the Palestinian territories|Palestine]], and [[War in Darfur|Sudan]]; the ongoing process of UN internal reform; and \"persistent...criticism against the UN\" and himself personally.<ref name=OffTheCuff /><ref name=NineMSN /> Annan's remarks came five days before the deadliest event of the year (and one of the deadliest natural disasters in history), the [[Indian Ocean tsunami]] on 26 December.\n\n== Juan Carlos I ==\nIn 2007, the [[Spanish Royal Family]], in particular [[Juan Carlos I of Spain|King Juan Carlos I]], faced a difficult year. Family tragedy and a series of controversies led to Spanish newspapers to refer to the year as the king's ''annus horribilis''.<ref name=\"La Naci\u00f3n\">''[http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias_v2/site/artic/20071115/pags/20071115203346.html El \"annus horribilis\" del Rey Juan Carlos]''. {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121206025748/http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias_v2/site/artic/20071115/pags/20071115203346.html |date=6 December 2012 }}, [[La Naci\u00f3n]], 15 November 2007.</ref>\n* In February, \u00c9rika Ortiz Rocasolano, the youngest sister of [[Queen Letizia of Spain|Letizia, then the Princess of Asturias]], died of a drug overdose in her apartment.\n* In July, a humour magazine, ''[[El Jueves]]'', published a drawing that ran on the cover, depicting [[Felipe VI of Spain|Felipe, Prince of Asturias (now Felipe VI of Spain)]], and the aforementioned Princess Letizia having sex, with a caption reading: \"Just imagine if you end up pregnant. This will be the closest thing to work I\u2019ve ever done in my life.\" It satirized a proposal by the government to give 2,500 euros to the parents of newborn children. The magazine was banned and removed from distribution, which led to a censorship controversy.\n* In September, [[Catalonia|Catalan]] separatists were tried for having burned photographs of King Juan Carlos and [[Queen Sof\u00eda of Spain|Queen Sof\u00eda]] at an anti-monarchy and Catalan separatist rally in [[Girona]] while the royal couple toured the city.\n* In early November at the XVII [[Ibero-American Summit]], after a verbal altercation between [[Hugo Ch\u00e1vez]], [[President of Venezuela]], and [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez Zapatero]], [[Prime Minister of Spain]], the king asked Ch\u00e1vez, \"''[[\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 no te callas?]]''\" (\"Why don't you shut up?\").\n* Shortly after the summit, the royal house announced the separation of the king's daughter, the [[Infanta Elena, Duchess of Lugo|Duchess of Lugo]], and her husband, [[Jaime de Marichalar]]. The couple have two children, [[Felipe Juan Froil\u00e1n de Marichalar y Borb\u00f3n|Felipe]] and [[Victoria de Marichalar y Borb\u00f3n|Victoria]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Latin phrases]]\n* [[Rampjaar]], the Dutch \"disaster year\" of 1672\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wiktionary|annus horribilis}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090302093837/http://www.royal.gov.uk/ImagesandBroadcasts/Historic%20speeches%20and%20broadcasts/Annushorribilisspeech24November1992.aspx Royal.gov.uk \u2013 Transcript of The Queen's speech at Guildhall 24 November 1992]\n*[http://www.hodderheadline.co.uk/bookdetails.asp?book=110295 ''Annus Horribilis'']{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}: book by [[Sam Jordison]]\n\n{{Elizabeth II}}\n\n[[Category:Latin words and phrases]]\n[[Category:1992 in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Spanish monarchy]]\n[[Category:Elizabeth II]]\n[[Category:2007 in Spain]]\n", "name_user": "ShermanPants", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annus_horribilis"}
{"title_page": "Evgraf Fedorov", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Evgraf Fedorov\n| image =Evgraf Fedorov Mondadori.jpg\n| caption = Evgraf Stepanovich Fedorov\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1853|12|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Orenburg]], [[Russian Empire]]\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1919|5|21|1853|12|22}}\n| death_place = [[Petrograd]], [[RSFSR]]\n}}\n'''Evgraf Stepanovich Fedorov''' ({{lang-ru|\u0415\u0432\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0301\u0444 \u0421\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0301\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0424\u0451\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432}}, {{OldStyleDate|22 December|1853|10 December}} \u2013 21 May 1919) was a Russian [[mathematician]], [[Crystallography|crystallographer]] and [[mineralogist]].<ref>I. I. Shafranovskii and N. V. Belov, \"In Memoriam: E. S. Fedorov 1853\u20131919,\" in P. P. Ewald, ed., ''Fifty Years of X-ray Diffraction'' (Utrecht, Nederland: International Union of Crystallography, 1962), pages 341\u2013350.  [http://www.iucr.org/__data/assets/pdf_file/0020/749/fedorov.pdf PDF online]</ref><ref>R.V. Galiulin (November 2003) \"To the 150th anniversary of the birth of Evgraf Stepanovich Federov (1853\u20131919):  Irregularities in the fate of the theory of regularity,\" ''Crystallography Reports'', '''48''' (6) : 899\u2013913. [http://www.galiulin.narod.ru/crys03_6.pdf.pdf PDF online]</ref><ref>A. Meniailov, \"Fyodorov (or Fedorov), Evgraf Stepanovich\" in Charles C. Gillispie, editor in chief, ''Dictionary of Scientific Biography'' (New York, New York:  Charles Scribner's Sons, 1972), vol. 5, pp.  210\u2013214.</ref>\n\nFedorov was born in the [[Russian Empire|Russian]] city of [[Orenburg]]. His father was a topographical engineer. The family later moved to [[Saint Petersburg]]. From the age of fifteen, he was deeply interested in the theory of [[polytope]]s, which later became his main research interest. He was a distinguished graduate of the [[Saint Petersburg Mining University|Gorny Institute]], which he joined at the age of&nbsp;26. He was elected the first Director of the Institute in 1905.<ref name=\"Profiles\">{{cite journal |last1=Biggart |first1=John |last2=John |first2=King |title=Profiles of Russian scientists and philosophers |journal=Alexander Boganov and the Origins of Systems Thinking in Russia |date=1998}}</ref>\n\nHe contributed to the identification of [[Periodic Graph (Geometry)#Obtaining periodicity|conditions under which a group of Euclidean motions must have a translational subgroup whose vectors span the Euclidean space]].  He undertook these investigations as early as 1881.<ref>See: \n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u00a7 55.  \u0415.\u0421. \u0424\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044a \u0441\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0438\u043b\u044a \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u0441\u043b\u0463\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f \u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0456\u0438 \u043d\u0463\u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0445\u044a \u0437\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u044a \u0433\u0435\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0438 \u043a\u044a \u0440\u0430\u0437\u044a\u044f\u0441\u043d\u0456\u044e \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f \u0434\u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445\u044a \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044a |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1882 |volume=17 |page=381 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3415357&view=1up&seq=393 |series=2nd series |trans-title=\u00a7 55. E.S. Fedorov reported his research on the application of certain laws of geometry to explain the formation of twin crystals. |language=Russian}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u00a7 62.  \u0415.\u0421. \u0424\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044a, \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0432\u044a \u0432\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0446\u0463 \u0441\u0443\u0449\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0438\u0437\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043c\u044a \u0433\u043e\u0434\u044a \u0442\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a \u0442\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0456\u044f \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043a\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b, \u043f\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u0437\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043d\u044b\u0430 \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0456\u044f \u0441\u0444\u0435\u0440\u044b \u0438\u043c\u0463\u044e\u0442\u044a \u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u044b \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0435\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044a (\u0442\u0440\u0438-, \u0442\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0430-, \u0433\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430-, \u0433\u0435\u043f\u0442\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0435\u0434\u0440\u044b) \u0438 \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0445\u044a \u0441\u0443\u0442\u044c \u0434\u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u044f \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044a, \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u043b\u044a \u043a\u044a \u0438\u0437\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0456\u044e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0456\u044f \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438\u0445\u044a \u0438\u0437\u0441\u043b\u0463\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439. |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1883 |volume=18 |pages=281 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3415358&view=1up&seq=291 |series=2nd series |trans-title=\u00a7 62. E.S. Fedorov \u2014 having briefly described the essence of the theory of crystalline structure presented by him a year ago, according to which the crystalline spheres have the form of parallohedra (tri-, tetra-, hexa-, heptaparallohedra) and whose planes are the twin planes of the crystal \u2014 proceeded to set forth the continuation of his research. |language=Russian}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u041d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0443\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0456\u044f \u043e \u0444\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0445\u044a |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1885 |volume=21 |pages=1-279 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3415360&view=1up&seq=5 |series=2nd series |trans-title=Elements of the theory of figures |language=Russian}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorow |first1=F. von |title=Zusammenstellung der kirstallographischen Resultate des Herrn Schoenflies und der meinigen |journal=Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Kristallographie und Mineralogie |date=1892 |volume=20 |pages=25-75 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3328306&view=1up&seq=41 |trans-title=Compilation of the crystallographic results of Mr. Schoenflies and mine |language=German}}; see footnote on p. 26.  From p. 26:  ''\"Diesem Gegenstande ist der vierte Abschnitt meiner \"Elemente der Lehre von den Figuren\" gewidmet, welcher schon 1881 fertig war, und in demselben Jahre habe ich davon schon Anwendung gemacht, und zwar darauf eine neue Theorie der Krytallstructur basirt (Verhandl. d. k. mineral. Ges. '''17''', 381 u. '''18''', 281).\"'' (The fourth part of my \"Elements of the Theory of Figures\", which was already finished in 1881, is devoted to this subject, and in the same year, I had already made use of it, and indeed [I had] based a new theory of crystal structure on it (Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society, '''17''', p. 381 and '''18''', p. 281).)</ref>  His best-known result is his 1891 derivation of the 230 symmetry [[space group]]s which now serve as the mathematical basis of [[X-ray crystallography|structural analysis]]. He also proved that there are only 17 possible [[wallpaper group]]s which can tile a [[Euclidean plane]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u0421\u0438\u043c\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0456\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1891 |volume=28 |pages=345\u2013390 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951t00080576a;view=1up;seq=357 |series=2nd series |trans-title=Simmetriya na ploskosti, Symmetry in the plane |language=Russian}}</ref> This was then proved independently by [[George P\u00f3lya]] in 1924.<ref>George P\u00f3lya (1924) \"\u00dcber die Analogie der Kristallsymmetrie in der Ebene\" (On the analog of crystal symmetry in the plane), ''Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Kristallographie'', '''60''' : 278\u2013282.</ref> The proof that the list of wallpaper groups was complete only came after the much harder case of space groups had been settled. In 1895, he became a professor of geology at the Moscow Agricultural Institute (now the [[Timiryazev Academy]]). Fedorov died from pneumonia in 1919 during the [[Russian Civil War]] in [[Petrograd]], [[RSFSR]].\n\nHe developed the [[Federov stage]] for polarizing microscopes, a tool for [[crystallography]] which allows a mineral specimen to be studied under precise angles of tilt and rotation, providing an analysis of crystal structure.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rruff.info/doclib/MinMag/Volume_29/29-209-150.pdf|title=An improved polarizing microscope IV. The Federov stage (three-axis)|journal=Mineralogical Magazine|year=1949|accessdate=September 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n*His first book, ''Basics of Polytopes'', was finished in 1879 and published in 1885. It offers a classification of [[polytope]]s and derives [[Fedorov polytopes]], congruent polytopes that can completely fill [[space]].\n*He wrote the classic ''The Symmetry of Regular Systems of Figures'' in 1891,<ref>E. S. Fedorov (1891) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951t00080576a;view=1up;seq=11 \"\u0421\u0438\u043c\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0456\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445\u044a \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u044a \u0444\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u044a\"] (''Simmetriya pravil'nykh sistem figur'', The symmetry of regular systems of figures), ''\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430'' (''Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva'', Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society), series 2, '''28''' : 1\u2013146. (in Russian)  English translation:  David and Katherine Harker (trans.), ''Symmetry of Crystals, American Crystallographic Association Monograph No. 7'' [Buffalo, N.Y.:  American Crystallographic Association, 1971], pages 50\u2013131.</ref> which contained the first cataloging of the 230 [[space groups]]. The same year the equivalent results were presented by German mathematician [[Arthur Moritz Sch\u00f6nflies|Sch\u00f6nflies]]. Fedorov and Sch\u00f6nflies had been intensively discussing the subject during their work, so the results can be somehow considered as joint ones, though Sch\u00f6nflies noted Fedorov's priority for some major ideas.\n*He published his classic work ''The Theodolite Method in Mineralogy and Petrography'' in 1893.<ref name=\"Kunz\">Kunz, George Frederick and [[Edgar T. Wherry|Wherry, Edgar T.]] (3 June 1921) \"Russian Geologists\" ''Science'', new series, '''53''' (1379):  516\u2013517</ref>\n* In 1906 he published ''Perfektsionizm'' (Perfectionism), a work he had started in the late 1870s. From a materialistic starting point he argued  that natural conditions are themselves conditions of eternal change. He attacked authors claim that there is  stability and equilibrium in nature. Contrariwise he claimed that evolution is quality of living creatures rather than a tendency toward a \"higher order\" of stability, and equilibrium of organisms. He criticised [[Herbert Spencer]]'s views arguing that such views when applied to the evolution of natural history focus attention on the least changeable. However, he argued that such views systematically failed to take into account the fact that equilibrium is attained only at the moment of death: for a living creature, changing forms are constantly developing. Thus Fyodorov criticised the notion that the constant and the stable are the supreme mission of life. Rather he claimed that life never finally achieves anything but always strives to achieve. For him this is where the true philosophy of nature is to be found.<ref name=\"Meniailov\">{{cite web |last1=Meniailov |first1=A. |title=Fyodorov (or Fedorov), Evgraf Stepanovich|url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/science/dictionaries-thesauruses-pictures-and-press-releases/fyodorov-or-fedorov-evgraf-stepanovich |website=www.encyclopedia.com |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n* ''Tsarstvo kristallov'' (Crystal Kingdom) was first published posthumously in 1920 and featured much of the work carried out by Fyodorov and his colleagues. during the previous of forty years. Here he noted that sciences which have been fully developed not only satisfy the spiritual needs of part of mankind but also provide great power to direct the active forces of nature for man\u2019s use.<ref name=\"Meniailov\"/>\n\n==Legacy==\n[[File:Evgraf-Fedorov-Stra\u00dfe.jpg|thumb|Evgraf Fjodorow Strasse]]\nThere is a street named after him on the site of the international X-ray laser research facility [[European XFEL]] in [[Schenefeld]] near [[Hamburg]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[Group theory]]\n* [[List of Russian material scientists]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Evgraf Fedorov}}\n* [http://www.minsoc.ru/2010/ Fedorov session 2010].\n* [http://www.minsoc.ru/fs2008/ Fedorov session 2008].\n* [http://www.minsoc.ru/fs2006/ Fedorov session 2006].\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110718155246/http://www.musoptin.com/fuess_universaldrehtisch_klein.html Small universal stage after Federow] for mineralogical microscopy, Berlin approx. 1900\n* [http://www.musoptin.com/fuess_universaldrehtisch.html Universal stage after Federow] for mineralogical microscopy, Berlin approx. 1925\n* [http://www.musoptin.com/fuess_4023.html Large microscope after Brand\u00e3o-Lei\u00df] with integrated universal stage after Fedorow, Berlin approx. 1925\n*{{in lang|ru}} [http://www.chem.msu.su/rus/cryst/cryshist/fedorov.htm Brief Biography]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fedorov, Evgraf Stepanovich}}\n[[Category:1853 births]]\n[[Category:1919 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Russian engineers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian engineers]]\n[[Category:Crystallographers]]\n[[Category:Deaths from pneumonia]]\n[[Category:Full Members of the Russian Academy of Sciences (1917\u201325)]]\n[[Category:People from Orenburg]]\n[[Category:People from Orenburg Governorate]]\n[[Category:Russian inventors]]\n[[Category:Russian mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Russian mineralogists]]\n[[Category:Russian mining engineers]]\n[[Category:Saint Petersburg Mining University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Evgraf Fedorov\n| image =Evgraf Fedorov Mondadori.jpg\n| caption = Evgraf Stepanovich Fedorov\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1853|12|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Orenburg]], [[Russian Empire]]\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1919|5|21|1853|12|22}}\n| death_place = [[Petrograd]], [[RSFSR]]\n}}\n'''Evgraf Stepanovich Fedorov''' ({{lang-ru|\u0415\u0432\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0301\u0444 \u0421\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0301\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0424\u0451\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432}}, {{OldStyleDate|22 December|1853|10 December}} \u2013 21 May 1919) was a Russian [[mathematician]], [[Crystallography|crystallographer]] and [[mineralogist]].<ref>I. I. Shafranovskii and N. V. Belov, \"In Memoriam: E. S. Fedorov 1853\u20131919,\" in P. P. Ewald, ed., ''Fifty Years of X-ray Diffraction'' (Utrecht, Nederland: International Union of Crystallography, 1962), pages 341\u2013350.  [http://www.iucr.org/__data/assets/pdf_file/0020/749/fedorov.pdf PDF online]</ref><ref>R.V. Galiulin (November 2003) \"To the 150th anniversary of the birth of Evgraf Stepanovich Federov (1853\u20131919):  Irregularities in the fate of the theory of regularity,\" ''Crystallography Reports'', '''48''' (6) : 899\u2013913. [http://www.galiulin.narod.ru/crys03_6.pdf.pdf PDF online]</ref><ref>A. Meniailov, \"Fyodorov (or Fedorov), Evgraf Stepanovich\" in Charles C. Gillispie, editor in chief, ''Dictionary of Scientific Biography'' (New York, New York:  Charles Scribner's Sons, 1972), vol. 5, pp.  210\u2013214.</ref>\n\nFedorov was born in the [[Russian Empire|Russian]] city of [[Orenburg]]. His father was a topographical engineer. The family later moved to [[Saint Petersburg]]. From the age of fifteen, he was deeply interested in the theory of [[polytope]]s, which later became his main research interest. He was a distinguished graduate of the [[Saint Petersburg Mining University|Gorny Institute]], which he joined at the age of&nbsp;26. He was elected the first Director of the Institute in 1905.<ref name=\"Profiles\">{{cite journal |last1=Biggart |first1=John |last2=John |first2=King |title=Profiles of Russian scientists and philosophers |journal=Alexander Boganov and the Origins of Systems Thinking in Russia |date=1998}}</ref>\n\nHe contributed to the identification of [[Periodic Graph (Geometry)#Obtaining periodicity|conditions under which a group of Euclidean motions must have a translational subgroup whose vectors span the Euclidean space]].  He undertook these investigations as early as 1881.<ref>See: \n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u00a7 55.  \u0415.\u0421. \u0424\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044a \u0441\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0438\u043b\u044a \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u0441\u043b\u0463\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f \u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0456\u0438 \u043d\u0463\u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0445\u044a \u0437\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u044a \u0433\u0435\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0438 \u043a\u044a \u0440\u0430\u0437\u044a\u044f\u0441\u043d\u0456\u044e \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f \u0434\u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445\u044a \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044a |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1882 |volume=17 |page=381 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3415357&view=1up&seq=393 |series=2nd series |trans-title=\u00a7 55. E.S. Fedorov reported his research on the application of certain laws of geometry to explain the formation of twin crystals. |language=Russian}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u00a7 62.  \u0415.\u0421. \u0424\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044a, \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0432\u044a \u0432\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0446\u0463 \u0441\u0443\u0449\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0438\u0437\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043c\u044a \u0433\u043e\u0434\u044a \u0442\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a \u0442\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0456\u044f \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043a\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b, \u043f\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u0437\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043d\u044b\u0430 \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0456\u044f \u0441\u0444\u0435\u0440\u044b \u0438\u043c\u0463\u044e\u0442\u044a \u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u044b \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0435\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044a (\u0442\u0440\u0438-, \u0442\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0430-, \u0433\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430-, \u0433\u0435\u043f\u0442\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0435\u0434\u0440\u044b) \u0438 \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0445\u044a \u0441\u0443\u0442\u044c \u0434\u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u044f \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044a, \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u043b\u044a \u043a\u044a \u0438\u0437\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0456\u044e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0456\u044f \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438\u0445\u044a \u0438\u0437\u0441\u043b\u0463\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439. |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1883 |volume=18 |pages=281 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3415358&view=1up&seq=291 |series=2nd series |trans-title=\u00a7 62. E.S. Fedorov \u2014 having briefly described the essence of the theory of crystalline structure presented by him a year ago, according to which the crystalline spheres have the form of parallohedra (tri-, tetra-, hexa-, heptaparallohedra) and whose planes are the twin planes of the crystal \u2014 proceeded to set forth the continuation of his research. |language=Russian}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u041d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0443\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0456\u044f \u043e \u0444\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0445\u044a |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1885 |volume=21 |pages=1-279 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3415360&view=1up&seq=5 |series=2nd series |trans-title=Elements of the theory of figures |language=Russian}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Fedorow |first1=F. von |title=Zusammenstellung der kirstallographischen Resultate des Herrn Schoenflies und der meinigen |journal=Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Kristallographie und Mineralogie |date=1892 |volume=20 |pages=25-75 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3328306&view=1up&seq=41 |trans-title=Compilation of the crystallographic results of Mr. Schoenflies and mine |language=German}}; see footnote on p. 26.  From p. 26:  ''\"Diesem Gegenstande ist der vierte Abschnitt meiner \"Elemente der Lehre von den Figuren\" gewidmet, welcher schon 1881 fertig war, und in demselben Jahre habe ich davon schon Anwendung gemacht, und zwar darauf eine neue Theorie der Krytallstructur basirt (Verhandl. d. k. mineral. Ges. '''17''', 381 u. '''18''', 281).\"'' (The fourth part of my \"Elements of the Theory of Figures\", which was already finished in 1881, is devoted to this subject, and in the same year, I had already made use of it, and indeed [I had] based a new theory of crystal structure on it (Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society, '''17''', p. 381 and '''18''', p. 281).)</ref>  His best-known result is his 1891 derivation of the 230 symmetry [[space group]]s which now serve as the mathematical basis of [[X-ray crystallography|structural analysis]]. He also proved that there are only 17 possible [[wallpaper group]]s which can tile a [[Euclidean plane]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Fedorov |first1=E.S. |title=\u0421\u0438\u043c\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0456\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 |journal=\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 (Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt-Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva, Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society) |date=1891 |volume=28 |pages=345\u2013390 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951t00080576a;view=1up;seq=357 |series=2nd series |trans-title=Simmetriya na ploskosti, Symmetry in the plane |language=Russian}}</ref> This was then proved independently by [[George P\u00f3lya]] in 1924.<ref>George P\u00f3lya (1924) \"\u00dcber die Analogie der Kristallsymmetrie in der Ebene\" (On the analog of crystal symmetry in the plane), ''Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Kristallographie'', '''60''' : 278\u2013282.</ref> The proof that the list of wallpaper groups was complete only came after the much harder case of space groups had been settled. In 1895, he became a professor of geology at the Moscow Agricultural Institute (now the [[Timiryazev Academy]]). Fedorov died from pneumonia in 1919 during the [[Russian Civil War]] in [[Petrograd]], [[RSFSR]].\n\nHe developed the [[Federov stage]] for polarizing microscopes, a tool for [[crystallography]] which allows a mineral specimen to be studied under precise angles of tilt and rotation, providing an analysis of crystal structure.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rruff.info/doclib/MinMag/Volume_29/29-209-150.pdf|title=An improved polarizing microscope IV. The Federov stage (three-axis)|journal=Mineralogical Magazine|year=1949|accessdate=September 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n*His first book, ''Basics of Polytopes'', was finished in 1879 and published in 1885. It offers a classification of [[polytope]]s and derives [[Fedorov polytopes]], congruent polytopes that can completely fill [[space]].\n*He wrote the classic ''The Symmetry of Regular Systems of Figures'' in 1891,<ref>E. S. Fedorov (1891) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951t00080576a;view=1up;seq=11 \"\u0421\u0438\u043c\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0456\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445\u044a \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u044a \u0444\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u044a\"] (''Simmetriya pravil'nykh sistem figur'', The symmetry of regular systems of figures), ''\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421.-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430'' (''Zapiski Imperatorskova Sankt Petersburgskova Mineralogicheskova Obshchestva'', Proceedings of the Imperial St. Petersburg Mineralogical Society), series 2, '''28''' : 1\u2013146. (in Russian)  English translation:  David and Katherine Harker (trans.), ''Symmetry of Crystals, American Crystallographic Association Monograph No. 7'' [Buffalo, N.Y.:  American Crystallographic Association, 1971], pages 50\u2013131.</ref> which contained the first cataloging of the 230 [[space groups]]. The same year the equivalent results were presented by German mathematician [[Arthur Moritz Sch\u00f6nflies|Sch\u00f6nflies]]. Fedorov and Sch\u00f6nflies had been intensively discussing the subject during their work, so the results can be somehow considered as joint ones, though Sch\u00f6nflies noted Fedorov's priority for some major ideas.\n*He published his classic work ''The Theodolite Method in Mineralogy and Petrography'' in 1893.<ref name=\"Kunz\">Kunz, George Frederick and [[Edgar T. Wherry|Wherry, Edgar T.]] (3 June 1921) \"Russian Geologists\" ''Science'', new series, '''53''' (1379):  516\u2013517</ref>\n* In 1906 he published ''Perfektsionizm'' (Perfectionism), a work he had started in the late 1870s. From a materialistic starting point he argued  that natural conditions are themselves conditions of eternal change. He attacked authors claim that there is  stability and equilibrium in nature. Contrariwise he claimed that evolution is quality of living creatures rather than a tendency toward a \"higher order\" of stability, and equilibrium of organisms. He criticised [[Herbert Spencer]]'s views arguing that such views when applied to the evolution of natural history focus attention on the least changeable. However, he argued that such views systematically failed to take into account the fact that equilibrium is attained only at the moment of death: for a living creature, changing forms are constantly developing. Thus Fyodorov criticised the notion that the constant and the stable are the supreme mission of life. Rather he claimed that life never finally achieves anything but always strives to achieve. For him this is where the true philosophy of nature is to be found.<ref name=\"Meniailov\">{{cite web |last1=Meniailov |first1=A. |title=Fyodorov (or Fedorov), Evgraf Stepanovich|url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/science/dictionaries-thesauruses-pictures-and-press-releases/fyodorov-or-fedorov-evgraf-stepanovich |website=www.encyclopedia.com |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n* ''Tsarstvo kristallov'' (Crystal Kingdom) was first published posthumously in 1920 and featured much of the work carried out by Fyodorov and his colleagues. during the previous of forty years. Here he noted that sciences which have been fully developed not only satisfy the spiritual needs of part of mankind but also provide great power to direct the active forces of nature for man\u2019s use.<ref name=\"Meniailov\"/>\n\n==Legacy==\n[[File:Evgraf-Fedorov-Stra\u00dfe.jpg|thumb|Evgraf Fjodorow Strasse]]\nThere is a street named after him on the site of the international X-ray laser research facility [[European XFEL]] in [[Schenefeld]] near [[Hamburg]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[Group theory]]\n* [[List of Russian material scientists]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Evgraf Fedorov}}\n* [http://www.minsoc.ru/2010/ Fedorov session 2010].\n* [http://www.minsoc.ru/fs2008/ Fedorov session 2008].\n* [http://www.minsoc.ru/fs2006/ Fedorov session 2006].\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110718155246/http://www.musoptin.com/fuess_universaldrehtisch_klein.html Small universal stage after Federow] for mineralogical microscopy, Berlin approx. 1900\n* [http://www.musoptin.com/fuess_universaldrehtisch.html Universal stage after Federow] for mineralogical microscopy, Berlin approx. 1925\n* [http://www.musoptin.com/fuess_4023.html Large microscope after Brand\u00e3o-Lei\u00df] with integrated universal stage after Fedorow, Berlin approx. 1925\n*{{in lang|ru}} [http://www.chem.msu.su/rus/cryst/cryshist/fedorov.htm Brief Biography]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fedorov, Evgraf Stepanovich}}\n[[Category:1853 births]]\n[[Category:1919 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Russian engineers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian engineers]]\n[[Category:Crystallographers]]\n[[Category:Deaths from pneumonia]]\n[[Category:Full Members of the Russian Academy of Sciences (1917\u201325)]]\n[[Category:People from Orenburg]]\n[[Category:People from Orenburg Governorate]]\n[[Category:Russian inventors]]\n[[Category:Russian mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Russian mineralogists]]\n[[Category:Russian mining engineers]]\n[[Category:Saint Petersburg Mining University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "VexorAbVikip\u00e6dia", "label": "safe", "comment": "Edited citations:  capitalization", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evgraf_Fedorov"}
{"title_page": "Norm Maleng", "text_new": "{{Infobox Officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = \n| name                = Norm Maleng\n| honorific-suffix    = \n| image               = \n| imagesize           = \n| smallimage          = \n| caption             = \n| order               = \n| office              = [[King County Prosecuting Attorney]]\n| term_start          = 1978\n| term_end            = 2007\n| president           = \n| succeeding          = \n| predecessor         = [[Chris Bayley]]\n| successor           = [[Dan Satterberg]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date|1938|09|17}}\n| birth_place         = [[Acme, Washington]], U.S.\n| death_date          = {{Death date and age|2007|05|24|1938|09|17}}\n| death_place         = [[Seattle, Washington]], U.S.\n| restingplace        = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| birthname           = \n| party               = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]]\n| spouse              = \n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = [[University of Washington]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]], [[Juris Doctor|JD]])\n| occupation          = [[Lawyer|Attorney]]\n| profession          = \n| cabinet             = \n| committees          = \n| portfolio           = \n| religion            = \n| signature           = \n| website             = \n| footnotes           = \n}}\n\n'''Norman Kim Maleng''' (September 17, 1938 &ndash; May 24, 2007) was an American attorney who served as the [[King County Prosecuting Attorney]] for 28 years.<ref name=\"Sullivan\">{{cite news|url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2003721534_normmaleng25.html|title=Longtime prosecutor Norm Maleng dies|last=Sullivan|first=Jennifer|author2=Steve Miletich |date=25 May 2007|publisher=[[The Seattle Times]]|accessdate=10 November 2010}}</ref> He was also an architect of Washington's Sentencing Reform Act.<ref name=\"Sullivan\"/>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nMaleng was born in [[Acme, Washington]], and grew up on a dairy farm. Known as \"Kim\" during his youth, he graduated from the [[University of Washington]] in 1960, then served as a lieutenant in the [[United States Army]]. He earned a [[Juris Doctor]] in 1966 from the [[University of Washington Law School]], serving as editor-in-chief of the ''Washington Law Review'' and graduating at the top of his class. \n\n==Career==\nHe worked in private practice in Seattle, and then as chief of the Civil Division of the Prosecutor's Office. In 1978, he was elected as Prosecutor, and was re-elected seven times.<ref name=\"Sullivan\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.metrokc.gov/proatty/nkm/bio.htm|title=Biography of Norm Maleng|work=King County Prosecuting Attorney's Office|accessdate=10 November 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070615004344/http://www.metrokc.gov/proatty/nkm/bio.htm|archivedate=15 June 2007}}</ref>\n\nMaleng was involved in a number of high-profile cases, including the 1983 [[Wah Mee massacre]], the [[2006 Seattle Jewish Federation shooting]] committed by [[Naveed Afzal Haq]], child sexual abuse allegations against [[King County Superior Court]] Judge [[Gary Little]], and the serial murders of [[Gary Ridgway]].\n\nMaleng's office made several controversial decisions not to prosecute various University of Washington football players over his tenure as King County Prosecuting Attorney, for alleged offenses that ranged from battery to sexual assault. His office declined to prosecute [[Jerramy Stevens]] for sexual assault, announcing on October 24, 2000, that no charges would be brought forward. Around 2008, Maryann Parker, the detective investigating the case, said: \"I thought [Jerramy] should have been charged. I think most people in the Police Department thought he should have been charged. From the police perspective, I think there was overwhelming evidence that a crime had occurred. And then I think we should have left it to a jury to decide. I think we just felt, in our unit and in the Police Department as a whole, that this case was handled differently. And we felt it was because he was a University of Washington football star.\u201d <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/seattle-news/convicted-of-assault-and-accused-of-rape-star-player-received-raft-of-second-chances/|title=Convicted of assault and accused of rape, star player received raft of second chances|date=2008-01-27|website=The Seattle Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\nHe ran for the Republican nomination for [[Governor of Washington]] in 1988 and 1996. In 1992, he lost an election for [[List of Attorneys General of Washington|Attorney General]] to [[Christine Gregoire]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.seattlepi.com/local/317243_maleng25.html|title=Norm Maleng dead at 68|last=Gutierrez|first=Scott|author2=Tracy Johnson |author3=Levi Pulkkinen |date=25 May 2007|publisher=[[Seattle Post-Intelligencer]]|accessdate=10 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nMaleng is credited with bringing several large scale policy reforms to Washington State's Criminal Justice system including passage of the 1984 Sentencing Reform Act, tougher penalties for car thefts in 2007 and rethinking the prosecution of low level drug offenses by placing emphasis on treatment options after a first or second offense, rather than lengthy prison sentences.\n\nAttorneys who worked for Maleng as deputy prosecuting attorneys include [[Marsha J. Pechman]], [[Robert S. Lasnik]] and [[Ricardo S. Martinez]], all judges of the [[U.S. District Court for the Western District of Washington]], and [[Dan Satterberg]], his successor\n\nMaleng supervised the wrongful conviction of Steve Titus. Titus was convicted of rape despite exculpatory evidence which established he could not have committed the crime. The conviction was overturned in June 1982 after Seattle Times reported Paul Henderson investigated and revealed evidence against Titus had been fabricated by police, with the knowledge of prosecutors. A complete account of the incident can be found in Predator, a book by Jack Olsen.\n\n==Death and honors==\nMaleng died of [[cardiac arrest]] during an event at the University of Washington on May 24, 2007.<ref name=\"Sullivan\"/> In December 2007, the King County Regional Justice Center in [[Kent, Washington|Kent]], was renamed in his honor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://your.kingcounty.gov/exec/news/2007/1201mrjc.aspx|title=Leaders gather to dedicate Norm Maleng Regional Justice Center|last=Sims|first=Ron|authorlink=Ron Sims|date=1 December 2007|work=kingcounty.gov|accessdate=18 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nLater in June 2008, [[Harborview Medical Center]] opened Norm Maleng Building on its campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washington.edu/news/2008/06/26/harborview-celebrates-opening-of-maleng-building|title=Harborview celebrates opening of Maleng Building|work=UW Today|date=June 26, 2008|accessdate=March 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\"Looking Back at the Titus Case\", Seattle Times, July 2, 1981\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Chris Bayley]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=King County Prosecuting Attorney|years=1978-2007}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Dan Satterberg]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maleng, Norm}}\n[[Category:1938 births]]\n[[Category:2007 deaths]]\n[[Category:Washington (state) lawyers]]\n[[Category:People from Whatcom County, Washington]]\n[[Category:People from King County, Washington]]\n[[Category:University of Washington alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Washington School of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:Washington (state) Republicans]]\n[[Category:United States Army officers]]\n[[Category:American prosecutors]]\n[[Category:Lawyers from Seattle]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = \n| name                = Norm Maleng\n| honorific-suffix    = \n| image               = \n| imagesize           = \n| smallimage          = \n| caption             = \n| order               = \n| office              = [[King County Prosecuting Attorney]]\n| term_start          = 1978\n| term_end            = 2007\n| president           = \n| succeeding          = \n| predecessor         = [[Chris Bayley]]\n| successor           = [[Dan Satterberg]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date|1938|09|17}}\n| birth_place         = [[Acme, Washington]], U.S.\n| death_date          = {{Death date and age|2007|05|24|1938|09|17}}\n| death_place         = [[Seattle, Washington]], U.S.\n| restingplace        = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| birthname           = \n| party               = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]]\n| spouse              = \n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = [[University of Washington]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]], [[Juris Doctor|JD]])\n| occupation          = [[Lawyer|Attorney]]\n| profession          = \n| cabinet             = \n| committees          = \n| portfolio           = \n| religion            = \n| signature           = \n| website             = \n| footnotes           = \n}}\n\n'''Norman Kim Maleng''' (September 17, 1938 &ndash; May 24, 2007) was an American attorney who served as the [[King County Prosecuting Attorney]] for 28 years.<ref name=\"Sullivan\">{{cite news|url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2003721534_normmaleng25.html|title=Longtime prosecutor Norm Maleng dies|last=Sullivan|first=Jennifer|author2=Steve Miletich |date=25 May 2007|publisher=[[The Seattle Times]]|accessdate=10 November 2010}}</ref> He was also an architect of Washington's Sentencing Reform Act.<ref name=\"Sullivan\"/>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nMaleng was born in [[Acme, Washington]], and grew up on a dairy farm. Known as \"Kim\" during his youth, he graduated from the [[University of Washington]] in 1960, then served as a lieutenant in the [[United States Army]]. He earned a [[Juris Doctor]] in 1966 from the [[University of Washington Law School]], serving as editor-in-chief of the ''Washington Law Review'' and graduating at the top of his class. \n\n==Career==\nHe worked in private practice in Seattle, and then as chief of the Civil Division of the Prosecutor's Office. In 1978, he was elected as Prosecutor, and was re-elected seven times.<ref name=\"Sullivan\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.metrokc.gov/proatty/nkm/bio.htm|title=Biography of Norm Maleng|work=King County Prosecuting Attorney's Office|accessdate=10 November 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070615004344/http://www.metrokc.gov/proatty/nkm/bio.htm|archivedate=15 June 2007}}</ref>\n\nMaleng was involved in a number of high-profile cases, including the 1983 [[Wah Mee massacre]], the [[2006 Seattle Jewish Federation shooting]] committed by [[Naveed Afzal Haq]], child sexual abuse allegations against [[King County Superior Court]] Judge [[Gary Little]], and the serial murders of [[Gary Ridgway]].\n\nMaleng's office made several controversial decisions not to prosecute various University of Washington football players over his tenure as King County Prosecuting Attorney, for alleged offenses that ranged from battery to sexual assault. His office declined to prosecute [[Jerramy Stevens]] for sexual assault, announcing on October 24, 2000, that no charges would be brought forward. Around 2008, Maryann Parker, the detective investigating the case, said: \"I thought [Jerramy] should have been charged. I think most people in the Police Department thought he should have been charged. From the police perspective, I think there was overwhelming evidence that a crime had occurred. And then I think we should have left it to a jury to decide. I think we just felt, in our unit and in the Police Department as a whole, that this case was handled differently. And we felt it was because he was a University of Washington football star.\u201d <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/seattle-news/convicted-of-assault-and-accused-of-rape-star-player-received-raft-of-second-chances/|title=Convicted of assault and accused of rape, star player received raft of second chances|date=2008-01-27|website=The Seattle Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\nHe ran for the Republican nomination for [[Governor of Washington]] in 1988 and 1996. In 1992, he lost an election for [[List of Attorneys General of Washington|Attorney General]] to [[Christine Gregoire]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.seattlepi.com/local/317243_maleng25.html|title=Norm Maleng dead at 68|last=Gutierrez|first=Scott|author2=Tracy Johnson |author3=Levi Pulkkinen |date=25 May 2007|publisher=[[Seattle Post-Intelligencer]]|accessdate=10 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nMaleng is credited with bringing several large scale policy reforms to Washington State's Criminal Justice system including passage of the 1984 Sentencing Reform Act, tougher penalties for car thefts in 2007 and rethinking the prosecution of low level drug offenses by placing emphasis on treatment options after a first or second offense, rather than lengthy prison sentences.\n\nAttorneys who worked for Maleng as deputy prosecuting attorneys include [[Marsha J. Pechman]], [[Robert S. Lasnik]] and [[Ricardo S. Martinez]], all judges of the [[U.S. District Court for the Western District of Washington]], and [[Dan Satterberg]], his successor\n\n==Death and honors==\nMaleng died of [[cardiac arrest]] during an event at the University of Washington on May 24, 2007.<ref name=\"Sullivan\"/> In December 2007, the King County Regional Justice Center in [[Kent, Washington|Kent]], was renamed in his honor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://your.kingcounty.gov/exec/news/2007/1201mrjc.aspx|title=Leaders gather to dedicate Norm Maleng Regional Justice Center|last=Sims|first=Ron|authorlink=Ron Sims|date=1 December 2007|work=kingcounty.gov|accessdate=18 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nLater in June 2008, [[Harborview Medical Center]] opened Norm Maleng Building on its campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washington.edu/news/2008/06/26/harborview-celebrates-opening-of-maleng-building|title=Harborview celebrates opening of Maleng Building|work=UW Today|date=June 26, 2008|accessdate=March 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\"Looking Back at the Titus Case\", Seattle Times, July 2, 1981\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Chris Bayley]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=King County Prosecuting Attorney|years=1978-2007}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Dan Satterberg]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maleng, Norm}}\n[[Category:1938 births]]\n[[Category:2007 deaths]]\n[[Category:Washington (state) lawyers]]\n[[Category:People from Whatcom County, Washington]]\n[[Category:People from King County, Washington]]\n[[Category:University of Washington alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Washington School of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:Washington (state) Republicans]]\n[[Category:United States Army officers]]\n[[Category:American prosecutors]]\n[[Category:Lawyers from Seattle]]\n", "name_user": "70.177.228.202", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eCareer)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norm_Maleng"}
{"title_page": "NXT Tag Team Championship", "text_new": "{{short description|Championship created by the American professional wrestling promotion WWE}}\n{{Infobox pro wrestling championship\n|name= NXT Tag Team Championship\n|image=NXT Tag Team Championship 2017.png\n|caption=The current NXT Tag Team Championship belt with default side plates <br>(2017\u2013present)\n|currentholder= The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]] and [[Timothy Thatcher]])\n|won= February 16, 2020\n|created=January 23, 2013\n|promotion=[[WWE]]\n|brand=[[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]]\n|firstchamp=British Ambition <small>([[Pac (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] and [[Joel Redman |Oliver Grey]])</small>\n|mostreigns=As team: [[The Undisputed Era]] (3)<br>As individual: [[Kyle O'Reilly]] (3)\n|longestreign=[[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] <small>([[Konnor (wrestler)|Conor O'Brian/Konnor]] and [[Viktor (wrestler)|Rick Victor/Viktor]])</small> (364 days{{efn|WWE officially recognizes it as 343 days, but still the longest.}})\n|shortestreign=[[British Strong Style|Moustache Mountain]] <small> ([[Tyler Bate]] and [[Trent Seven]]) </small> (2 days{{efn|WWE officially recognizes it as 22 days, but still the shortest.}})\n|oldest=[[Bobby Fish]] ({{age in years and days|1976|10|27|2019|08|15}})|youngest=[[Tyler Bate]] ({{age in years and days|1997|03|07|2018|06|19}})\n|heaviest=[[The Authors of Pain]] {{small|([[Akam (wrestler)|Akam]] and [[Rezar (wrestler)|Rezar]])}} (620 lbs combined)\n|lightest=[[The Lucha Dragons]] {{small|([[Kalisto (wrestler)|Kalisto]] and [[Sin Cara]])}} (368 lbs combined)\n|pastlookimages=\n}}\nThe '''NXT Tag Team Championship''' is a [[professional wrestling]] [[tag team]] [[Professional wrestling championship|championship]] created and promoted by the [[United States|American]] [[professional wrestling promotion|promotion]] [[WWE]], defended on their [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] [[WWE brand extension|brand]]. It is one of three male tag team championships among WWE's three main brands, along with the [[WWE Raw Tag Team Championship]] on [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and the [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship]] on [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]. The current champions are The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]] and [[Timothy Thatcher]]), they are in their first reign; however, due to a travel ban as a result of the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]], [[Timothy Thatcher]] is defending the titles alongside Riddle until Dunne's return.\n\nIntroduced on January 23, 2013, the title was established as the men's tag team championship for NXT, which at the time was a [[Farm team|developmental territory]] for WWE. The inaugural champions were British Ambition ([[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] and [[Joel Redman|Oliver Grey]]). Over the years, NXT grew to become WWE's third major brand, which became official in September 2019 when NXT was moved to the [[USA Network]].\n\n== History ==\n{{multiple image\n|align = right\n|direction = vertical\n|header =\n|width = 150\n|image1 = Neville March 2015 (cropped).jpg\n|caption1 =\n|image2 = Joel Redman.jpg\n|caption2 = The inaugural NXT Tag Team Champions, the British Ambition: [[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] (top) and [[Oliver Grey]] (bottom)\n}}\nIn June 2012, the [[WWE]] established [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] as their [[Farm team|developmental territory]], replacing [[Florida Championship Wrestling]] (FCW). The following year on the January 23 episode of ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]]'', special guest and [[WWE Hall of Fame]]r [[Shawn Michaels]] announced that there would be an eight-team [[single-elimination tournament|single-elimination]] [[Professional wrestling tournament|tournament]] to crown the first NXT Tag Team Champions.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bishop|first=Matt|title=WWE NXT: HBK kicks off tag title tournament|url=http://slam.canoe.ca/Slam/Wrestling/2013/01/24/20523731.html|work=SLAM! Wrestling|accessdate=January 25, 2013}}</ref> On the January 31 taping of ''NXT'' ([[Broadcast delay|aired]] February 13), British Ambition ([[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] and [[Oliver Grey]]) defeated [[The Wyatt Family]] ([[Luke Harper]] and [[Erick Rowan]]) in the tournament final to become the inaugural champions.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT results 2/13 \u2013 Week 33: First NXT tag champions crowned, Paige vows to take over the show|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_68672.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref> In the first title defense, however, Neville and [[Bo Dallas]] defended the title against The Wyatt Family due to Grey being injured, where they lost; Dallas was not recognized as champion.<ref name=NXT050213Spoilers>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/77312/wwe-nxt-spoilers-from-winter-park-fl-john-cena-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE NXT spoilers from Winter Park, FL: John Cena and more|last=Santiago|first=Andres|date=3 May 2013|accessdate=3 May 2013|work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 5/8 Week 45: Wyatt Family captures Tag Titles, Ohno turning face?, Sandow in action, Paige vs. Summer Rae feud continues, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_70553.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref> On the June 20 taping of ''NXT'' (aired July 17), Neville and [[Corey Graves]] defeated The Wyatt Family for the title, making Neville the first two-time champion.<ref name=\"Neville2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_71434.shtml|title=WWE News: NXT spoilers for summer episodes \u2013 first NXT Women's champ, Flair, more, plus NXT TV in the U.S.?|last=Caldwell|first=James|date=21 June 2013|accessdate=26 June 2013|work=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> On June 8, 2016, [[The Revival (professional wrestling)|The Revival]] ([[Scott Dawson (wrestler)|Scott Dawson]] and [[Dash Wilder]]) became the first team to hold the championship on more than one occasion when they defeated [[American Alpha]] ([[Chad Gable]] and [[Jason Jordan]]) at [[NXT TakeOver: The End|TakeOver: The End]].\n\nAlthough NXT had been established as WWE's developmental territory, over the years it grew to establish itself as WWE's third major brand. This would become official in September 2019 when NXT was moved to the [[USA Network]], thus making the NXT Tag Team Championship the third major tag team title for men in the WWE, along with the [[WWE Raw Tag Team Championship]] and [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/wrestling/triple-h-discusses-nxt-as-a-third-brand-putting-talent-in-a-position-to-succeed-more/|title=Triple H Discusses NXT as a Third Brand, Putting Talent in a Position to Succeed, More \u2013 411MANIA|website=www.411mania.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Inaugural tournament ===\n<onlyinclude>{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n|team-width = 200px\n|RD1-team1  = '''[[The Wyatt Family]]<br>{{small|([[Luke Harper]] and [[Erick Rowan]])}}'''\n|RD1-score1 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=74584&p=1|title=DX invades DX taping: Complete WWE NXT spoilers from Florida|last=Santiago|first=Andres|date=2013-01-11|accessdate=2013-02-01|work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref>\n|RD1-team2  = [[Percy Watson]] and [[Yoshi Tatsu]]\n|RD1-score2 =\n|RD1-team3  = '''[[Bo Dallas]] and [[Curtis Axel|Michael McGillicutty]]'''\n|RD1-score3 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD1-team4  = [[Primo & Epico]]\n|RD1-score4 =\n|RD1-team5  = '''British Ambition<br>{{small|([[Adrian Neville]] and [[Oliver Grey]])}}'''\n|RD1-score5 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD1-team6  = 3MB<br>{{small|([[Drew Galloway|Drew McIntyre]] and [[Heath Slater]])}}\n|RD1-score6 =\n|RD1-team7  = '''[[Chris Hero|Kassius Ohno]] and [[Adam Rose|Leo Kruger]]'''\n|RD1-score7 = Sub<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD1-team8  = [[Alex Riley]] and [[Ethan Carter III|Derrick Bateman]]\n|RD1-score8 =\n|RD2-team1  = '''The Wyatt Family<br>{{small|(Luke Harper and Erick Rowan)}}'''\n|RD2-score1 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD2-team2  = Bo Dallas and Michael McGillicutty\n|RD2-score2 =\n|RD2-team3  = '''British Ambition<br>{{small|(Adrian Neville and Oliver Grey)}}'''\n|RD2-score3 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD2-team4  = Kassius Ohno and Leo Kruger\n|RD2-score4 =\n|RD3-team1  = The Wyatt Family<br>{{small|(Luke Harper and Erick Rowan)}}\n|RD3-score1 =\n|RD3-team2  = '''British Ambition<br>{{small|(Adrian Neville and Oliver Grey)}}'''\n|RD3-score2 = Pin\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Belt design==\n[[File:Blake & Murphy May 2015.jpg|thumb|right|270px|One-time champions [[Blake and Murphy]] (right and left), shown here with the original NXT Tag Team Championship belts]]\nThe original NXT Tag Team Championship belts featured a simple design. The center plate was an irregular polygon. Prominently down the center of the plate was a vertical NXT logo in gold; to the left center side of the logo read \"Tag\" while the right center side read \"Team\". The two side plates contained the WWE logo. The plates were on a black leather strap. A unique feature of this original design was that the two belts were slightly different. On one belt, the left side of the center plate was black with \"Tag\" written in gold while the right side of the center plate was gold with \"Team\" written in black; the other belt was the opposite. The side plates also reflected this coloring; the side plate on the black side was dominated by a black background behind the WWE logo while the side plate on the gold side had a dominant gold background behind the WWE logo. When first introduced, the side plates had the WWE scratch logo but in August 2014, all of WWE's pre-existing championships at the time received a minor update, changing the scratch logo to WWE's new logo originally used for the [[WWE Network]].\n\nOn April 1, 2017, at [[WrestleMania Axxess]], [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] General Manager [[William Regal]] announced that all of the NXT title belts would be redesigned. The new title belts were unveiled at [[NXT TakeOver: Orlando|TakeOver: Orlando]] that same night and given to the winners of their respective matches. Both the center plate and side plates of the new NXT Tag Team Championship belts are the same shape as the previous design and are again on black leather straps. The differences are the design on the plates themselves. The center plate maintains the vertical NXT logo prominently in the center, but now in silver with the WWE logo affixed at the very center of the \"X\". At the top of the plate right above the vertical NXT logo is a banner that reads \"Tag Team\", while at the bottom of the plate below the logo is a banner that reads \"Champions\". Black, silver, and gold ornamentation fills in the rest of the plate. Unlike the previous design, both belts are exactly the same. Coming in line with the majority of WWE's other championship belts, the updated design features side plates with a removable center section that can be customized with the champion's logo; the default side plates feature the WWE logo. As a result, the championship was the first WWE tag team championship to feature customizable side plates.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/wwe/videos/10154635435021443/|title=EXCLUSIVE: WWE NXT General William Regal arrives at WrestleMania Axxess with a HUGE announcement regarding NXT TakeOver: Orlando!|date=April 1, 2017|author=[[WWE]]|work=[[Facebook]]|accessdate=April 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Reigns == \n{{main|List of NXT Tag Team Champions}}\nAs of {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}}  {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}}, there have been 20 reigns between 17 teams composed of 35 individual champions, and one vacancy. [[The Undisputed Era]] as a stable have the most reigns at three, while individually, stable member [[Kyle O'Reilly]] has the most reigns, also at three. The inaugural champions were the British Ambition (Adrian Neville and [[Oliver Grey]]). The team with the longest reign is [[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] ([[Konnor (wrestler)|Conor O'Brian/Konnor]] and [[Viktor (wrestler)|Rick Victor/Viktor]]), who held the title for 364 days,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73685.shtml#.UmPZpvmTjTp|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 10/2: New NXT Tag champions|date=2013-02-10|accessdate=2013-10-20|publisher=PWTorch}}</ref><ref name=fataldark>{{cite web|last1=Caldwell|first1=James|title=NXT news: NXT Title match result, Kenta gets new ring name, new Tag Champs, main roster champ wrestles, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_80587.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref> while the shortest reign belongs to Moustache Mountain ([[Tyler Bate]] and [[Trent Seven]]), who held the title for 2 days. However, due to [[Broadcast delay|tape delays]], which are the dates that WWE recognizes for the NXT Tag Team Championship's history, they recognize that The Ascension's reign was 343 days and that Moustache Mountain's reign was 22 days, which are still the longest and shortest reigns regardless. Tyler Bate holds the record as the youngest champion when he won it at 21, while the oldest is [[Bobby Fish]] when he won it at 42.\n\nThe current champions are The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]] and [[Timothy Thatcher]]), who are in their first reign. They won the titles\n\n==See also==\n* [[Tag team championships in WWE]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-tag-team-championship Official NXT Tag Team Championship Title History]\n\n{{NXT Tag Team Championship}}\n{{NXT Championships}}\n\n[[Category:WWE NXT championships]]\n[[Category:Tag team wrestling championships]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Championship created by the American professional wrestling promotion WWE}}\n{{Infobox pro wrestling championship\n|name= NXT Tag Team Championship\n|image=NXT Tag Team Championship 2017.png\n|caption=The current NXT Tag Team Championship belt with default side plates <br>(2017\u2013present)\n|currentholder= The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]])\n|won= February 16, 2020\n|created=January 23, 2013\n|promotion=[[WWE]]\n|brand=[[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]]\n|firstchamp=British Ambition <small>([[Pac (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] and [[Joel Redman |Oliver Grey]])</small>\n|mostreigns=As team: [[The Undisputed Era]] (3)<br>As individual: [[Kyle O'Reilly]] (3)\n|longestreign=[[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] <small>([[Konnor (wrestler)|Conor O'Brian/Konnor]] and [[Viktor (wrestler)|Rick Victor/Viktor]])</small> (364 days{{efn|WWE officially recognizes it as 343 days, but still the longest.}})\n|shortestreign=[[British Strong Style|Moustache Mountain]] <small> ([[Tyler Bate]] and [[Trent Seven]]) </small> (2 days{{efn|WWE officially recognizes it as 22 days, but still the shortest.}})\n|oldest=[[Bobby Fish]] ({{age in years and days|1976|10|27|2019|08|15}})|youngest=[[Tyler Bate]] ({{age in years and days|1997|03|07|2018|06|19}})\n|heaviest=[[The Authors of Pain]] {{small|([[Akam (wrestler)|Akam]] and [[Rezar (wrestler)|Rezar]])}} (620 lbs combined)\n|lightest=[[The Lucha Dragons]] {{small|([[Kalisto (wrestler)|Kalisto]] and [[Sin Cara]])}} (368 lbs combined)\n|pastlookimages=\n}}\nThe '''NXT Tag Team Championship''' is a [[professional wrestling]] [[tag team]] [[Professional wrestling championship|championship]] created and promoted by the [[United States|American]] [[professional wrestling promotion|promotion]] [[WWE]], defended on their [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] [[WWE brand extension|brand]]. It is one of three male tag team championships among WWE's three main brands, along with the [[WWE Raw Tag Team Championship]] on [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and the [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship]] on [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]. The current champions are The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]]), who are in their first reign; however, due to a travel ban as a result of the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]], [[Timothy Thatcher]] is defending the titles alongside Riddle until Dunne's return.\n\nIntroduced on January 23, 2013, the title was established as the men's tag team championship for NXT, which at the time was a [[Farm team|developmental territory]] for WWE. The inaugural champions were British Ambition ([[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] and [[Joel Redman|Oliver Grey]]). Over the years, NXT grew to become WWE's third major brand, which became official in September 2019 when NXT was moved to the [[USA Network]].\n\n== History ==\n{{multiple image\n|align = right\n|direction = vertical\n|header =\n|width = 150\n|image1 = Neville March 2015 (cropped).jpg\n|caption1 =\n|image2 = Joel Redman.jpg\n|caption2 = The inaugural NXT Tag Team Champions, the British Ambition: [[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] (top) and [[Oliver Grey]] (bottom)\n}}\nIn June 2012, the [[WWE]] established [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] as their [[Farm team|developmental territory]], replacing [[Florida Championship Wrestling]] (FCW). The following year on the January 23 episode of ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]]'', special guest and [[WWE Hall of Fame]]r [[Shawn Michaels]] announced that there would be an eight-team [[single-elimination tournament|single-elimination]] [[Professional wrestling tournament|tournament]] to crown the first NXT Tag Team Champions.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bishop|first=Matt|title=WWE NXT: HBK kicks off tag title tournament|url=http://slam.canoe.ca/Slam/Wrestling/2013/01/24/20523731.html|work=SLAM! Wrestling|accessdate=January 25, 2013}}</ref> On the January 31 taping of ''NXT'' ([[Broadcast delay|aired]] February 13), British Ambition ([[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]] and [[Oliver Grey]]) defeated [[The Wyatt Family]] ([[Luke Harper]] and [[Erick Rowan]]) in the tournament final to become the inaugural champions.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT results 2/13 \u2013 Week 33: First NXT tag champions crowned, Paige vows to take over the show|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_68672.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref> In the first title defense, however, Neville and [[Bo Dallas]] defended the title against The Wyatt Family due to Grey being injured, where they lost; Dallas was not recognized as champion.<ref name=NXT050213Spoilers>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/77312/wwe-nxt-spoilers-from-winter-park-fl-john-cena-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE NXT spoilers from Winter Park, FL: John Cena and more|last=Santiago|first=Andres|date=3 May 2013|accessdate=3 May 2013|work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 5/8 Week 45: Wyatt Family captures Tag Titles, Ohno turning face?, Sandow in action, Paige vs. Summer Rae feud continues, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_70553.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref> On the June 20 taping of ''NXT'' (aired July 17), Neville and [[Corey Graves]] defeated The Wyatt Family for the title, making Neville the first two-time champion.<ref name=\"Neville2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_71434.shtml|title=WWE News: NXT spoilers for summer episodes \u2013 first NXT Women's champ, Flair, more, plus NXT TV in the U.S.?|last=Caldwell|first=James|date=21 June 2013|accessdate=26 June 2013|work=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> On June 8, 2016, [[The Revival (professional wrestling)|The Revival]] ([[Scott Dawson (wrestler)|Scott Dawson]] and [[Dash Wilder]]) became the first team to hold the championship on more than one occasion when they defeated [[American Alpha]] ([[Chad Gable]] and [[Jason Jordan]]) at [[NXT TakeOver: The End|TakeOver: The End]].\n\nAlthough NXT had been established as WWE's developmental territory, over the years it grew to establish itself as WWE's third major brand. This would become official in September 2019 when NXT was moved to the [[USA Network]], thus making the NXT Tag Team Championship the third major tag team title for men in the WWE, along with the [[WWE Raw Tag Team Championship]] and [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/wrestling/triple-h-discusses-nxt-as-a-third-brand-putting-talent-in-a-position-to-succeed-more/|title=Triple H Discusses NXT as a Third Brand, Putting Talent in a Position to Succeed, More \u2013 411MANIA|website=www.411mania.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Inaugural tournament ===\n<onlyinclude>{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n|team-width = 200px\n|RD1-team1  = '''[[The Wyatt Family]]<br>{{small|([[Luke Harper]] and [[Erick Rowan]])}}'''\n|RD1-score1 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=74584&p=1|title=DX invades DX taping: Complete WWE NXT spoilers from Florida|last=Santiago|first=Andres|date=2013-01-11|accessdate=2013-02-01|work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref>\n|RD1-team2  = [[Percy Watson]] and [[Yoshi Tatsu]]\n|RD1-score2 =\n|RD1-team3  = '''[[Bo Dallas]] and [[Curtis Axel|Michael McGillicutty]]'''\n|RD1-score3 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD1-team4  = [[Primo & Epico]]\n|RD1-score4 =\n|RD1-team5  = '''British Ambition<br>{{small|([[Adrian Neville]] and [[Oliver Grey]])}}'''\n|RD1-score5 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD1-team6  = 3MB<br>{{small|([[Drew Galloway|Drew McIntyre]] and [[Heath Slater]])}}\n|RD1-score6 =\n|RD1-team7  = '''[[Chris Hero|Kassius Ohno]] and [[Adam Rose|Leo Kruger]]'''\n|RD1-score7 = Sub<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD1-team8  = [[Alex Riley]] and [[Ethan Carter III|Derrick Bateman]]\n|RD1-score8 =\n|RD2-team1  = '''The Wyatt Family<br>{{small|(Luke Harper and Erick Rowan)}}'''\n|RD2-score1 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD2-team2  = Bo Dallas and Michael McGillicutty\n|RD2-score2 =\n|RD2-team3  = '''British Ambition<br>{{small|(Adrian Neville and Oliver Grey)}}'''\n|RD2-score3 = Pin<ref name=NXTTagTournament/>\n|RD2-team4  = Kassius Ohno and Leo Kruger\n|RD2-score4 =\n|RD3-team1  = The Wyatt Family<br>{{small|(Luke Harper and Erick Rowan)}}\n|RD3-score1 =\n|RD3-team2  = '''British Ambition<br>{{small|(Adrian Neville and Oliver Grey)}}'''\n|RD3-score2 = Pin\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Belt design==\n[[File:Blake & Murphy May 2015.jpg|thumb|right|270px|One-time champions [[Blake and Murphy]] (right and left), shown here with the original NXT Tag Team Championship belts]]\nThe original NXT Tag Team Championship belts featured a simple design. The center plate was an irregular polygon. Prominently down the center of the plate was a vertical NXT logo in gold; to the left center side of the logo read \"Tag\" while the right center side read \"Team\". The two side plates contained the WWE logo. The plates were on a black leather strap. A unique feature of this original design was that the two belts were slightly different. On one belt, the left side of the center plate was black with \"Tag\" written in gold while the right side of the center plate was gold with \"Team\" written in black; the other belt was the opposite. The side plates also reflected this coloring; the side plate on the black side was dominated by a black background behind the WWE logo while the side plate on the gold side had a dominant gold background behind the WWE logo. When first introduced, the side plates had the WWE scratch logo but in August 2014, all of WWE's pre-existing championships at the time received a minor update, changing the scratch logo to WWE's new logo originally used for the [[WWE Network]].\n\nOn April 1, 2017, at [[WrestleMania Axxess]], [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] General Manager [[William Regal]] announced that all of the NXT title belts would be redesigned. The new title belts were unveiled at [[NXT TakeOver: Orlando|TakeOver: Orlando]] that same night and given to the winners of their respective matches. Both the center plate and side plates of the new NXT Tag Team Championship belts are the same shape as the previous design and are again on black leather straps. The differences are the design on the plates themselves. The center plate maintains the vertical NXT logo prominently in the center, but now in silver with the WWE logo affixed at the very center of the \"X\". At the top of the plate right above the vertical NXT logo is a banner that reads \"Tag Team\", while at the bottom of the plate below the logo is a banner that reads \"Champions\". Black, silver, and gold ornamentation fills in the rest of the plate. Unlike the previous design, both belts are exactly the same. Coming in line with the majority of WWE's other championship belts, the updated design features side plates with a removable center section that can be customized with the champion's logo; the default side plates feature the WWE logo. As a result, the championship was the first WWE tag team championship to feature customizable side plates.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/wwe/videos/10154635435021443/|title=EXCLUSIVE: WWE NXT General William Regal arrives at WrestleMania Axxess with a HUGE announcement regarding NXT TakeOver: Orlando!|date=April 1, 2017|author=[[WWE]]|work=[[Facebook]]|accessdate=April 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Reigns == \n{{main|List of NXT Tag Team Champions}}\nAs of {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}}  {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}}, there have been 20 reigns between 17 teams composed of 35 individual champions, and one vacancy. [[The Undisputed Era]] as a stable have the most reigns at three, while individually, stable member [[Kyle O'Reilly]] has the most reigns, also at three. The inaugural champions were the British Ambition (Adrian Neville and [[Oliver Grey]]). The team with the longest reign is [[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] ([[Konnor (wrestler)|Conor O'Brian/Konnor]] and [[Viktor (wrestler)|Rick Victor/Viktor]]), who held the title for 364 days,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73685.shtml#.UmPZpvmTjTp|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 10/2: New NXT Tag champions|date=2013-02-10|accessdate=2013-10-20|publisher=PWTorch}}</ref><ref name=fataldark>{{cite web|last1=Caldwell|first1=James|title=NXT news: NXT Title match result, Kenta gets new ring name, new Tag Champs, main roster champ wrestles, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_80587.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref> while the shortest reign belongs to Moustache Mountain ([[Tyler Bate]] and [[Trent Seven]]), who held the title for 2 days. However, due to [[Broadcast delay|tape delays]], which are the dates that WWE recognizes for the NXT Tag Team Championship's history, they recognize that The Ascension's reign was 343 days and that Moustache Mountain's reign was 22 days, which are still the longest and shortest reigns regardless. Tyler Bate holds the record as the youngest champion when he won it at 21, while the oldest is [[Bobby Fish]] when he won it at 42.\n\nThe current champions are The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]]), who are in their first reign. They won the titles by defeating [[The Undisputed Era]]'s [[Bobby Fish]] and [[Kyle O'Reilly]] at [[NXT TakeOver: Portland]] on February 16, 2020 in [[Portland, Oregon]]. Due to a travel ban as a result of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], [[Timothy Thatcher]] is defending the titles alongside Riddle until Dunne's return, but Thatcher is not recognized as champion.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Tag team championships in WWE]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-tag-team-championship Official NXT Tag Team Championship Title History]\n\n{{NXT Tag Team Championship}}\n{{NXT Championships}}\n\n[[Category:WWE NXT championships]]\n[